```xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<manifest xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    package="com.autoscout904703.facebook-auto-post-tool">

    <!-- 
       The application name displayed to users. 
       This app serves as a social media management tool for automating content scheduling operations on Facebook.
    -->
    <application
        android:allowBackup="true"
        android:icon="@mipmap/ic_launcher"
        android:label="@string/app_name"
        android:roundIcon="@mipmap/ic_launcher_round"
        android:supportsRtl="true"
        android:theme="@style/AppTheme">
        
        <!-- Main activity that serves as the entry point of the application -->
        <activity android:name=".MainActivity">
            <intent-filter>
                <action android:name="android.intent.action.MAIN" />
                <category android:name="android.intent.category.LAUNCHER" />
            </intent-filter>
        </activity>

        <!-- Background service for automation tasks -->
        <service android:name=".AutomationService" />
    </application>

    <!-- Permissions required for the application to function correctly -->
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.INTERNET"
        tools:ignore="ProtectedPermissions" />
    <!-- 
        Permission to access the internet is needed to connect with Facebook and other social media platforms 
        for content scheduling and operations.
    -->

    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE"
        tools:ignore="ProtectedPermissions" />
    <!-- 
        This permission allows the app to check the state of network connectivity
        to ensure successful background operations.
    -->

    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE"
        tools:ignore="ProtectedPermissions" />
    <!-- 
        Permission to write to external storage is required for saving logs or media files related to scheduling tasks.
    -->

    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE"
        tools:ignore="ProtectedPermissions" />
    <!-- 
        This permission allows the application to read media files from the external storage, 
        essential for content management tasks.
    -->

</manifest>
```

### Explanation of Manifest Configuration:

- **Application Tag**: This contains the configuration settings for the application such as the app's name, icon, and theme. It registers the main activity and service components.
- **MainActivity**: The entry point of the application where users will interact with the app's user interface.
- **AutomationService**: A background service designed for handling automated content scheduling tasks, ensuring continuous operation compliant with social media management guidelines.
- **Permissions**: 
  - `INTERNET`: Necessary for network operations related to the appâ€™s functionality in social media management.
  - `ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE`: To monitor the network state, ensuring the app can perform its functions seamlessly.
  - `WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE` and `READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE`: Required to manage files that may be utilized for automation tasks, such as storing configurations or logs.

This configuration is designed to support the functionality of the Facebook auto post tool, emphasizing compliance with best practices for social media management and automation.
